transcript.text: Open your file in Corel Draw.
Use Bezier tool to draw a path.
Create a path with your preferred shape.
Edit the path by dragging its notes and make your design accordingly.
Set properties of path using outline tool.
You can also use shortcut F-12 to edit properties of outline.
Copy the path and paste it in a new document.
Set resolution to 72 DPI.
Resize the page that fits to your designed shape.
Set height and width of the pages per the size of path.
Click on OK.
Now place the path in center of document.
You can use shortcut P to set the path in center of page.
Select the path and export it in SVG format.
Click on export.
Your document is saved at desktop.
Open the document using Edit with Notepad++.
Copy this path to paste it into Custom Properties window.
In PDF Block plugin.
Open your PDF file with Adobe Acrobat.
Click on PD Flib Blocks menu.
Draw one block using PD flip block.
Pledge in.
While drawing this path, consider the below points.
One block should cover highest left of path.
Two blocks should cover highest right of path.
Three blocks should cover highest bottom of path 4.
Top of the block is variable.
Match right, left and bottom blocks perfectly with the borders of path.
Click on Expand all button.
Set block properties using property window.
Enter your preferred text at default text area.
Set alignment of the text.
Also add custom properties using this window.
Click on Add button to set custom properties.
Enter click path in property name.
Use zoom in and zoom out.
Set block at highest left of path.
Set block at highest right of path.
Block is variable at top.
Now PDF file is ready, we can upload this file.
